CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1774627872
OL,3,CEndangered red panda's 'blind date' in
OL,4,Chopes of protecting the species
OL,6,FRed pandas look more similar to
OL,7,Fracoons, having long, bushy tails,
OL,8,Fpatterned with 12 alternating rich red
OL,9,Fand buff coloured ring.
OL,11,FThey were discovered more than 50
OL,12,Fyears before the giant panda and only
OL,13,Fshare the name due to a distant common
OL,14,Fancestor that lived millions of years
OL,15,Fago.
OL,17,FToday they are found in mountainous
OL,18,Fregions of Nepal, India, Bhutan,
OL,19,FMyanmar and southern China.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
